Swindon.title: Swindon
Swindon.byline: Swindon is a large town in Wiltshire, south west England, that is known for its railway-town heritage and links with the British railway system in which it played a central part during the 19th and 20th centuries.

Swiss Alps.title: Swiss Alps
Swiss Alps.byline: The Swiss Alps are in Switzerland, stretching over several regions.

Switzerland.title: Switzerland
Switzerland.byline: Switzerland (German: Schweiz, French: Suisse, Italian: Svizzera, Romansch: Svizra), is a mountainous country known globally for its neutrality, democracy, and its almost-legendary affluence: Switzerland has one of the highest standards of living in the world, and prices to match.

Swiss Alps Jungfrau-Aletsch.title: Swiss Alps Jungfrau-Aletsch
Swiss Alps Jungfrau-Aletsch.byline: Swiss Alps Jungfrau-Aletsch is a protected area and a UNESCO World Heritage Site between the Valais and the Bernese Highlands in the Swiss Alps.

Swiss National Park.title: Swiss National Park
Swiss National Park.byline: Swiss National Park is the only national park in Switzerland, located in Graubünden canton.
